{"type":"message","id":"6d4ae852","parentId":"1a53e74e","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:40:03.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Let me just use the correct tool <|tool_calls_section_begin|> <|tool_call_begin|> functionsread6 <|tool_call_argument_begin|> {\"file_path\": \"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\", \"limit\": 30} <|tool_call_end|> <|tool_call_begin|> functionsedit7 <|tool_call_argument_begin|> {\"file_path\": \"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\", \"oldText\": \"## Every Session\\nBefore doing anything else:\\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\\n3. Read `memory/daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\", \"newText\": \"## Every Session\\nBefore doing anything else:\\n1. **Run `./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh`** — recover context from compaction\\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\\n3. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\\n5. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\"} <|tool_call_end|> <|tool_call_begin|> functionsedit8 <|tool_call_argument_begin|> {\"file_path\": \"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\", \"old_string\": \"*Updated: 2026-02-22*\", \"new_text\": \"---\\n\\n## Context Anchor Skill v1.1\\n**Installed:** 2026-03-10 | **Version:** 1.1.0 | **Location:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nRecover from context compaction by scanning memory files and surfacing where you left off. Supports both flat (YYYY-MM-DD.md) and QMD hierarchical (daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md) memory structures.\\n\\n### Key Features\\n- **Dual Structure Support:** Automatically detects and handles both flat and hierarchical memory paths\\n- **Fast Recovery:** Generates comprehensive \\\"where you left off\\\" briefing in seconds\\n- **Multiple View Modes:**\\n  - `--task`: Current task focus only\\n  - `--active`: Active context files summary\\n  - `--decisions`: Recent decisions extracted\\n  - `--loops`: Open questions and blockers\\n\\n### Integration Points\\n| File | Integration |\\n|------|-------------|\\n| `AGENTS.md` | Added to \\\"Every Session\\\" startup routine (step 1) |\\n| `MEMORY.md` | Documentation and usage notes |\\n| `qmd://`** | Scanned for context recovery |\\n\\n### Usage\\n```bash\\n# Full context briefing (default)\\n./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh\\n\\n# Specific views\\n./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh --task\\n./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh --active\\n./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh --decisions\\n./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh --loops\\n\\n# Scan 5 days back\\n./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor-v2.sh --days 5\\n```\\n\\n### Memory Collections Used\\n- `qmd://daily/` — Session notes and conversations\\n- `memory/context/active/` — In-progress tasks\\n- `memory/context/decisions/` — Important decisions\\n- `qmd://projects/` — YouTube, GitHub, CRM work\\n- `qmd://reference/` — Curated reference docs\\n\\n### Why This Matters\\nSession compaction loses transient memory. Files survive, but after waking up fresh, you need:\\n1. Know what you were working on\\n2. See decisions that were made\\n3. Find open loops that need closing\\n4. Get oriented fast\\n\\nThis skill automates that recovery by scanning memory files and generating a structured briefing.\\n\\n*Updated: 2026-03-10*\"} <|tool_call_end|> <|tool_calls_section_end|>","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773106722431}}
